replies.body:
I would buy the argument that Rito simply couldn't do anything because these cheaters could make bots faster than Rito could ban them, except half these bots were level 30+ and 40+. Now, co-op sans FWotD bonus gives very little experience. It takes literally _months_ of FWotD bonuses and/or _hundreds_ of co-op games to be rocking the levels some of these bots are rocking.

For these bots to get that far, Rito has to be basically sitting on their hands doing **NOTHING** about them.

{{sticker:zombie-nunu-bummed}} 

 - - -

If Rito were actually bothering to detect and to ban these bots, then setting level requirements for higher "difficulty" (haha) co-op might give players the option to use higher "difficulty" co-op relatively free from bots for testing and such, and only Intro and such would be flooded with new bots on their way to their eventual bans.

However, since bots are allowed free reign in LoL, going months and/or hundreds of games without bans, that's not really an option.

{{sticker:sg-janna}} 

 - - -

The really sad part is that half of these bots actually qualify for Ranked play. I feel bad for the Iron players if the cheaters decide to unleash their bot army upon Ranked Runeterra someday.

{{sticker:sg-soraka}}
